00:18.070 --> 00:21.000
My brother wants to hear
France's terms for peace.

00:22.189 --> 00:23.309
This is good news.

00:25.380 --> 00:28.339
Majesty, now is the time to tell
the King about our negotiating...

00:28.340 --> 00:29.450
He is not well enough.

00:29.460 --> 00:31.581
- That is precisely why we need to...
- Not yet.

00:39.400 --> 00:41.509
Your physician says
a sip is enough, Majesty.

00:43.390 --> 00:44.450
Louis...

00:46.420 --> 00:47.450
Enough.

00:52.520 --> 00:54.320
It hurts.

01:00.017 --> 01:01.360
Can you make it stop?

01:02.410 --> 01:03.420
No.

01:10.500 --> 01:12.400
But I will not leave your side.

01:14.370 --> 01:15.450
Please, Aramis...

01:18.480 --> 01:20.300
One more time.

01:29.719 --> 01:31.689
As soon as we have the
Spanish terms we go to him,

01:31.714 --> 01:33.784
this is becoming too dangerous.

01:36.246 --> 01:38.430
The Ambassador expects you at dawn.

01:56.520 --> 01:58.440
Seems in order.

01:58.450 --> 02:02.410
So, these are the
murderous Spanish generals?

02:02.420 --> 02:05.310
I trust they were handed over
without incident?

02:05.390 --> 02:06.450
Mmm.

02:06.553 --> 02:07.582
And now they are yours.

02:07.607 --> 02:08.607
Mmm.

02:13.360 --> 02:15.340
Easy.

02:16.300 --> 02:17.499
Easy!

02:17.500 --> 02:21.350
Spanish or not, they're still
prisoners of war, Marcheaux!

02:21.360 --> 02:24.510
- Hey.
- Treat them as you'd wish to be treated.

02:24.903 --> 02:28.803
Hundreds of French soldiers were
slaughtered in their custody.

02:29.500 --> 02:31.470
But they deserve better from us.

02:32.320 --> 02:33.370
Don't they?

02:34.420 --> 02:36.330
Until they hang.

02:39.380 --> 02:42.934
Oh, there'll be hell to pay if the people's
thirst for justice isn't appeased.

